subject: Thank you for applying to Coinbase
body:
Hi Emily,

Thank you for showing interest in joining our team and taking the time to apply to Coinbase.

We'll be reviewing your application shortly and will reach out to you on any next steps if your qualifications match our needs for the role.

Global Data Privacy Notice for Job Candidates and Applicants

Depending on your location, the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) may regulate the way we manage the data of job applicants. Our full notice outlining how your data will be processed as part of the application procedure for application locations is available here: Ireland/EU ( https://static-assets.coinbase.com/privacy_notice_and_consent_for_new_applicants_coinbase_ireland.pdf ), United Kingdom ( https://static-assets.coinbase.com/privacy_notice_and_consent_for_new_applicants_CB_payments.pdf ), and California ( https://static-assets.coinbase.com/notice_at_collection_to_applicants_residing_in_california_CCPA.pdf ). By submitting your application, you are agreeing to our use and processing of your data as required.

Regards,
Coinbase

** Please note: Do not reply to this email. This email is sent from an unattended mailbox. Replies will not be read.

body:
Hi Emily Fang,

Thanks for applying to Google! There are a ton of great companies out  
there, so we appreciate your interest in joining our team.

While we’re not able to reach out to every applicant, our recruiting team  
will contact you if your skills and experience are a strong match for the  
role. In the meantime, join the conversation about job opportunities and  
life at Google on our LinkedIn page:  
https://www.linkedin.com/company/google/.

Thanks,

Google Staffing


Learn more about our Equal Employment Opportunity policy:  
https://careers.google.com/eeo/ and the EEOC's "Equal Employment

Google's Pay Transparency Policy ensures that you won't be discharged or

https://careers.google.com/static/files/paytransparency.pdf

applicant and candidate privacy policy:  
https://careers.google.com/privacy-policy/.

body:

subject: Thank you for your application to Oliver Space
body:
Hi Emily,

Thank you for your interest in Oliver Space! We wanted to let you know we received your application for Frontend Software Engineer, and we are delighted that you would consider joining our team.

Our team will review your application and will be in touch if your qualifications match our needs for the role. If you are not selected for this position, keep an eye on our jobs page as we're growing and adding openings.

Best,

The Oliver Space Team

label: jobs
subject: Thank you for applying to Capsule
body:
Hi Emily,

Thank you for your interest in Capsule. We received your application and we’re thrilled that you’re considering joining us on our mission to build a pharmacy that works for everyone ( https://medium.com/capsule-cares/a-pharmacy-that-works-for-everyone-everywhere-4fb2b54e2566 ). We’ll review your application and will be in touch if your skills and experiences align with the needs of the role.

In the meantime, we encourage you to sign up for Capsule and use our product ( https://capsule.com/get-started?_branch_match_id=883086618431660381 ). Experiencing our customer journey firsthand will enable a more productive interview process.

We appreciate you considering opportunities at Capsule and will be in touch soon.

Love,

Capsule

** Please note: Do not reply to this email. This email is sent from an unattended mailbox. Replies will not be read.

subject: Thanks for applying to Stripe!
body:
Hi Emily,

Thanks so much for submitting your application for the New Grad Software Engineer role! As a reminder, we have recorded your location preference (San Francisco, Seattle, New York, or Toronto) based on your application responses so only one application is required.

With the high volume of applications, our University Recruiting team will review applications on a rolling basis which may cause a delay in our response times. We appreciate your understanding and, in the meantime, encourage you to check out our quick guide to Stripe culture [0], our blog[1], and our LinkedIn page[2] to get a feel for what we're up to at Stripe.

We hope to connect soon!

Stripe

subject: Thanks for applying to Squarespace’s New Grad Opportunity!
body:
Hey Emily,

Thanks for your interest in a New Grad role at Squarespace!

What happens now? Our Early Career Recruiting Team will review your application as quickly as possible and reach out if there's a good match. While you wait, check out the below info to learn more about your new grad experience at Squarespace!

New Grad Life at Squarespace

Joining as a New Grad at Squarespace means contributing meaningful work, growing your professional skill set, and exploring all that NYC has to offer! You will be embedded into a small team of engineers of all levels from day one. Through mentorship, detailed code reviews, and collaboration with teammates, you will ramp up in no time!

While we review your application, check out our Early Career Recruiting page ( https://www.squarespace.com/careers/early-career ) to learn more about what it means to join as a New Grad at Squarespace! You can also learn more about Squarespace’s company culture by reading what makes us one of the top 100 Best Places to Work ( https://www.builtinnyc.com/companies/best-places-to-work-nyc-2021 ).

Thanks!

The Squarespace Early Career Recruiting Team

subject: Software Engineer - Web Platform - Rokt
body:
Hi Emily,

Thank you for your interest in working at Rokt!

The first step of our process is a short aptitude assessment - it only
takes 15 minutes. It's part of Rokt's company-wide holistic interview
practices and helps guide the later stages of our interviews.

The assessment is sent via email directly from "Criteria Corp" and must be
taken at one time - so we recommend finding a time when you won't be
interrupted.

I will send it to you now; please let me know if you do not receive it or
if you've received this email twice.

Best,

Sahana Sudhakar

label: jobs
subject: Thanks for applying to Squarespace’s New Grad Opportunity!
body:
Hey Emily,

Thanks for your interest in a New Grad role at Squarespace!

What happens now? Our Early Career Recruiting Team will review your application as quickly as possible and reach out if there's a good match. While you wait, check out the below info to learn more about your new grad experience at Squarespace!

New Grad Life at Squarespace

Joining as a New Grad at Squarespace means contributing meaningful work, growing your professional skill set, and exploring all that NYC has to offer! You will be embedded into a small team of engineers of all levels from day one. Through mentorship, detailed code reviews, and collaboration with teammates, you will ramp up in no time!

While we review your application, check out our Early Career Recruiting page ( https://www.squarespace.com/careers/early-career ) to learn more about what it means to join as a New Grad at Squarespace! You can also learn more about Squarespace’s company culture by reading what makes us one of the top 100 Best Places to Work ( https://www.builtinnyc.com/companies/best-places-to-work-nyc-2021 ).

Thanks!

The Squarespace Early Career Recruiting Team

Newsroom ( https://blog.squarespace.com/ ) | LinkedIn ( https://www.linkedin.com/company/squarespace/ ) | Blog ( http://squarespace.com/blog ) |Engineering ( https://engineering.squarespace.com/ ) |Creative ( https://creative.squarespace.com/blog )
